It's got off to an encouraging start with lots of excitement and plenty of goals. But a bigger challenge in the sport may lie away from the pitch, in governance. 

Although FIFA has a female secretary general, only two football associations are led by women and one of them, Sierra Leone's Isha Johansen, claims she has been the victim of a government plot to get rid of her. 

The BBC's Alex Capstick met up with her at the World Cup in Paris... --BBC--